1
00:00:08,916 --> 00:00:11,625
♪

2
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:45,083
Huh? Is that Kuboyasu?

3
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:47,583
I don't care for the way
he's standing there all creepy.

4
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:49,000
It's no biggie.

5
00:01:49,083 --> 00:01:51,875
He still shows a lot of promise
for someone so frail.

6
00:01:51,958 --> 00:01:53,333
If he were properly motivated,

7
00:01:53,416 --> 00:01:55,458
I could turn him into
a first-class soldier.

8
00:01:55,541 --> 00:01:57,541
Dark Reunion
won't know what hit 'em

9
00:01:57,625 --> 00:01:59,750
when I lead my righteous army
into the final battle.

10
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:00,958
Hey.

11
00:02:01,041 --> 00:02:02,708
[THUG]
Show some respect, kid.

12
00:02:02,791 --> 00:02:05,083
A simple "sorry" don't cut it
when you bump into us.

13
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:07,541
I think you broke my arm. That's
like a million yen to fix.

14
00:02:07,625 --> 00:02:10,333
--Did you hear that?
--Give me a million yen.

15
00:02:10,416 --> 00:02:13,291
Oh, crap. Those guys
are shaking down Kuboyasu.

16
00:02:13,375 --> 00:02:14,833
But I can't turn a blind eye
to evil,

17
00:02:14,916 --> 00:02:17,375
especially in my neighborhood,
so I will...

18
00:02:17,458 --> 00:02:19,333
go find a hero
who can actually help.

19
00:02:19,416 --> 00:02:20,708
[THUG 1]
Aah! We're sorry!

20
00:02:20,791 --> 00:02:22,708
Hey, wait.
I'm a hero who can help.

21
00:02:22,791 --> 00:02:24,291
[THUG 2]
Forgive us.

22
00:02:24,375 --> 00:02:26,083
Let go of his throat.
You're gonna kill him.

23
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:28,041
[whimpers]

24
00:02:28,125 --> 00:02:29,750
[grunts and groans,
punches landing]

25
00:02:31,416 --> 00:02:34,041
What? What the heck
just happened?

26
00:02:34,125 --> 00:02:36,000
I had no idea he was like this.

27
00:02:36,083 --> 00:02:38,166
Oh, man.

28
00:02:39,208 --> 00:02:40,541
Did this morning
really happen?

29
00:02:40,625 --> 00:02:42,291
I knew he had promise,
but I never thought

30
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:44,083
Kuboyasu had such
fighting skills.

31
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:46,750
Thinking back, lots of little
things have been weird with him.

32
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:49,291
When he arrived, he introduced
himself with phrases like,

33
00:02:49,375 --> 00:02:51,291
"S'up, homeys,"
and "Aren was here."

34
00:02:51,375 --> 00:02:53,583
On Festival Day, he said
he got ketchup on himself,

35
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:55,708
but it didn't smell
anything like ketchup.

36
00:02:55,791 --> 00:02:58,125
I also think that "huh" that
sometimes appears over his head

37
00:02:58,208 --> 00:02:59,333
is really weird.

38
00:02:59,416 --> 00:03:00,541
[SAIKI]
You can see that?

39
00:03:00,625 --> 00:03:02,166
What's going on, little guy?

40
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:04,250
Aah! What? Don't sneak up on me
like that!

41
00:03:04,333 --> 00:03:06,083
Well, you can always come to me
for advice.

42
00:03:06,166 --> 00:03:08,750
[SAIKI] I can't think of
a worse guy to go to for advice.

43
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,791
--Well, it's...
--Wow, you really are.

44
00:03:10,875 --> 00:03:12,916
Do you think something's up
with Kuboyasu?

45
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,208
Huh? What about me?

46
00:03:14,291 --> 00:03:15,708
Aah! Nothing.

47
00:03:15,791 --> 00:03:17,750
--S'up, new guy?
--What are you guys doing?

48
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:19,166
I want in on it.

49
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:22,333
Has he always been this scary?
It's not important, sir.

50
00:03:22,416 --> 00:03:24,000
Sir? What's with
the formal talk, dude?

51
00:03:24,083 --> 00:03:25,208
[whimpers]

52
00:03:25,291 --> 00:03:27,000
You're acting kind of strange.

53
00:03:27,083 --> 00:03:28,541
Did something happen?

54
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,375
Did you maybe see something
you shouldn't have?

55
00:03:30,458 --> 00:03:32,458
What's wrong, stupid?
You scared?

56
00:03:32,541 --> 00:03:35,166
You're the stupid one.
I got a little dizzy is all.

57
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,416
--He's a weirdo, right?
--I guess.

58
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:37,958
Get off it, Nendou.

59
00:03:38,041 --> 00:03:40,625
What are you going on about?
All I hear is crazy talk.

60
00:03:40,708 --> 00:03:41,916
[sneezes]

61
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,333
Ooh, that was a wet one.

62
00:03:43,416 --> 00:03:45,625
Nendou! You okay?

63
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:47,708
Yeah, I'm fine. No big deal.

64
00:03:47,791 --> 00:03:49,125
Apologize to him.

65
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:50,375
Hold on.
My nose is still itching.

66
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:52,000
Oh, you got some on your face.

67
00:03:52,083 --> 00:03:53,583
That's full of snot too!

68
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:55,166
Really, I'm fine.
It's just a sneeze.

69
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:56,833
After all that, he's not mad.

70
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:59,250
Can someone so level-headed
really be a juvenile delinquent?

71
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:00,833
I said...

72
00:04:00,916 --> 00:04:02,500
[SAIKI] You're barely
holding it together.

73
00:04:02,583 --> 00:04:04,375
We take showers
after P.E., anyway.

74
00:04:04,458 --> 00:04:05,791
Guess I was wrong about him.

75
00:04:05,875 --> 00:04:08,125
He's so shy
about changing his clothes.

76
00:04:08,208 --> 00:04:09,583
Heck, maybe that wasn't even him

77
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:12,000
I saw beating up those guys
this morning.

78
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:13,541
Yeah, I was mistaken.

79
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:15,875
[NENDOU] Dude, why do you
take off your shirt like a--

80
00:04:15,958 --> 00:04:17,916
Hey, give that back to me.

81
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,708
He's totally ripped
from the neck down!

82
00:04:19,791 --> 00:04:21,625
I heard we're playing
baseball today.

83
00:04:21,708 --> 00:04:23,708
Maybe he just likes
to lift weights.

84
00:04:23,791 --> 00:04:25,666
Plenty of normal
non-delinquents do that, right?

85
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:29,125
Why is he looking at that bat
like it's an old friend?

86
00:04:29,208 --> 00:04:30,666
Could he be thinking,

87
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,791
"I never thought I'd use you
for an actual baseball"?

88
00:04:32,875 --> 00:04:35,958
Oh, crap. I think Kuboyasu's
really a delinquent.

89
00:04:36,041 --> 00:04:39,208
Even the way he squats
is vaguely thuggish.

90
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:41,708
--[grunts]
--Kuboyasu, are you okay?

91
00:04:41,791 --> 00:04:44,125
If he's a delinquent, there's
about to be a huge fight.

92
00:04:44,208 --> 00:04:46,250
--Watch where you're throwing.
--You hit him, you hit us.

93
00:04:46,333 --> 00:04:49,541
There's not gonna be a fight.
That's just baseball.

94
00:04:49,625 --> 00:04:51,791
Now, where were we?
No outs. Runner on first.

95
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:53,958
Now he sounds like
a reformed delinquent

96
00:04:54,041 --> 00:04:55,333
in a teen sports drama!

97
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:58,541
Whoa, thunderstorm.
Everyone inside.

98
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:01,333
Damn. We could've won that game.

99
00:05:01,416 --> 00:05:02,875
Are you a loner too?

100
00:05:02,958 --> 00:05:05,166
Why is there suddenly
an abandoned puppy

101
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:06,625
after it started raining?

102
00:05:08,166 --> 00:05:09,333
I'm certain of it now.

103
00:05:09,416 --> 00:05:10,958
He's definitely
a delinquent.

104
00:05:11,041 --> 00:05:13,291
All these weeks, he's pretended
to be a normal kid

105
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:14,916
while hiding
a powerful dark side.

106
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,833
[SAIKI] Isn't that how
you imagine your own life?

107
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:19,041
[KAIDOU] I'll have to keep
my distance from him now.

108
00:05:19,125 --> 00:05:20,666
More for his good than mine.

109
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:23,083
If he ever messed with me,
I could go full Jet Black Wings

110
00:05:23,166 --> 00:05:24,541
and turn him into ashes.

111
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:25,750
Yeah, I'd like to see that.

112
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:27,166
Oh, hey, Saiki,
do you want to go--

113
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:29,083
--Afternoon, fellas.
--There's a new rule.

114
00:05:29,166 --> 00:05:31,250
You got to pay the toll
if you want to walk through.

115
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:32,458
[whimpers]

116
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:33,916
Get back here.

117
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,291
We can't have you forgetting to
pay now, either.

118
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:38,458
What? Oh, no.

119
00:05:38,541 --> 00:05:41,750
Saiki and I are
getting shaken down for money.

120
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:44,750
♪

121
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:49,583
If you want to get through, pay
up. Whatever's in your pockets.

122
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:52,000
Looks like trouble
found us again, huh?

123
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:54,500
These juvenile delinquents are
from the worst school in town.

124
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:56,125
Saiki's scared, always is.

125
00:05:56,208 --> 00:05:59,250
I'd use my power,
but it's just too dangerous.

126
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:01,333
--Pay up, dumbass.
--Shun, no!

127
00:06:01,416 --> 00:06:04,166
--[THUG] Take that.
--[SAIKI] Shun!

128
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:06,583
What's with this kid?

129
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,166
We must've punched him
a hundred times.

130
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:10,500
How the hell is he standing?

131
00:06:10,583 --> 00:06:11,708
Is he superhuman?

132
00:06:11,791 --> 00:06:13,166
[HYAKKIMARU] Well, what's this?

133
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:14,625
[THUG]
Hyakkimaru.

134
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:16,333
Looks like you started
the party without me.

135
00:06:16,416 --> 00:06:18,291
Well, now I'm getting in
on the fun.

136
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:20,791
We just roughed him up. You hit
him with that, you'll kill him.

137
00:06:20,875 --> 00:06:23,666
[laughs]
Good point. I'll hit him.

138
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,125
[gasps]

139
00:06:25,208 --> 00:06:26,333
[snickers]

140
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:28,833
Oh. Hey,
what happened to my arm?

141
00:06:28,916 --> 00:06:30,083
[ALL] Hyakkimaru!

142
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:31,875
So if you like to
shake down innocent kids,

143
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:34,958
then you have yourself to blame
for what happens after this.

144
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:37,041
As a parting gift before
I send you to the Netherworld,

145
00:06:37,125 --> 00:06:38,625
I'll show you the power
of Black Beat--

146
00:06:38,708 --> 00:06:40,375
Hey. Hey, are you listening?

147
00:06:40,458 --> 00:06:42,083
Feeble-minded fools.

148
00:06:42,166 --> 00:06:44,125
It's far too late
for you powerless weaklings

149
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:45,791
to escape from me.

150
00:06:45,875 --> 00:06:48,000
[THUG] I said give us the money
if you want to get through.

151
00:06:48,083 --> 00:06:49,750
[SAIKI] Time to come back
to Earth, Shun.

152
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,625
What's that?
Didn't I take all you guys down?

153
00:06:51,708 --> 00:06:53,375
What? Stop screwing around
with us, losers.

154
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:54,791
Where's Hyakkimaru?

155
00:06:54,875 --> 00:06:56,583
Never heard of him.
Now give us our money.

156
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,958
Hyakkimaru might show up
in delinquent manga,

157
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:00,041
but not in this anime.

158
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:02,375
Wait. All of that before
was my fantasy?

159
00:07:02,458 --> 00:07:04,083
[THUG]
You think you're better than us?

160
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:06,000
Wait. If Hyakkimaru
doesn't exist,

161
00:07:06,083 --> 00:07:08,750
I can stop these small-timers
easily using my normal powers.

162
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:10,125
This is your last chance, buddy.

163
00:07:10,208 --> 00:07:11,625
What? You're gonna hit me
with that?

164
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:13,125
I won't if you give us
your wallet.

165
00:07:13,208 --> 00:07:15,041
I'm outnumbered. Of all
the times to get mugged,

166
00:07:15,125 --> 00:07:17,458
it had to happen
when Saiki was around.

167
00:07:17,541 --> 00:07:19,791
If he wasn't with me,
I'd just hand over everything.

168
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:21,666
--You would?
--But Saiki looks up to me.

169
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,250
I have to take on
these delinquents

170
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:24,541
and show them my cool side.

171
00:07:24,625 --> 00:07:25,750
You don't have
a cool side.

172
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:27,333
My wallet isn't here!

173
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:29,583
[wimpy voice] There it is,
in my back pocket all along.

174
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:31,583
--Who would've thought?
--You're exhausting.

175
00:07:31,666 --> 00:07:33,000
[THUG 1] Whoa, you carry
a lot of cash.

176
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:34,666
[THUG 2] Your daddy
rich or something?

177
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,541
[SAIKI] That could pay for
a lot of coffee jelly.

178
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:37,791
Now it's your turn, pal.

179
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:39,458
Hey, you got enough for today.

180
00:07:39,541 --> 00:07:41,541
Shut it,
unless you want to get hit.

181
00:07:41,625 --> 00:07:43,208
Your friend finally gave us
his wallet.

182
00:07:43,291 --> 00:07:45,875
Now you're gonna do the same,
okay? Hey, knock that off.

183
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:47,708
All right,
you're finally playing ball.

184
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:49,208
That wasn't so hard, was it?

185
00:07:49,291 --> 00:07:52,000
Too bad I cursed your body
so that in three months,

186
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:53,791
blood will come out of
every pore.

187
00:07:53,875 --> 00:07:55,625
Consider this wallet my apology.

188
00:07:55,708 --> 00:07:58,208
--Then I guess we're done--
--Aah! Let's go!

189
00:07:58,291 --> 00:07:59,583
Hey, hold it!

190
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:03,958
--[KAIDOU] Aah! Unhand me!
--[THUG] This kid's really slow.

191
00:08:04,041 --> 00:08:06,458
He's so slow, you wonder
if he's trying to get caught.

192
00:08:06,541 --> 00:08:07,875
Oh, well. Sorry, Kaidou.

193
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:09,833
I'm gonna keep running
and just go home.

194
00:08:09,916 --> 00:08:11,666
[THUG] You're not coming back
for your friend?

195
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:13,166
He's not really my friend.

196
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:15,333
You do realize we're gonna
beat up your pal, right?

197
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:18,750
Oh, good. I'm glad at least
you managed to get away, Saiki.

198
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:21,083
Seriously.
I can't leave him now.

199
00:08:21,166 --> 00:08:23,916
He stopped. So he does
have a heart after all.

200
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,916
I've hidden it for long enough.
Time to reveal my true powers.

201
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,375
Or I can just leave you
to this guy.

202
00:08:30,458 --> 00:08:32,916
--It's easier for me, anyway.
--Hey, what's going on here?

203
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:35,708
What? A shakedown.

204
00:08:35,791 --> 00:08:37,625
Kuboyasu's here.
Excellent timing.

205
00:08:37,708 --> 00:08:39,125
He's a lot stronger
than he looks.

206
00:08:39,208 --> 00:08:40,541
I bet he could save me.

207
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:42,625
Oh, hey. Are you friends
with these losers?

208
00:08:42,708 --> 00:08:45,083
Kuboyasu,
don't just stand there. Run.

209
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:47,833
--Get out of here now.
--I can't ask him for help.

210
00:08:47,916 --> 00:08:50,958
I'm just messing around.
It's fine.

211
00:08:51,041 --> 00:08:52,708
I can't make him fight for me.

212
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:54,625
after I've spent the last day
trying to avoid him.

213
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:56,875
You run away with Saiki
while you still can.

214
00:08:56,958 --> 00:08:58,791
These guys aren't a big deal,
so I can handle them.

215
00:08:58,875 --> 00:09:00,375
[THUG 1]
Are you threatening us?

216
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:01,958
[THUG 2]
Not too bright, is he?

217
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:04,708
Whoa. Hold on.
We can't just let you go.

218
00:09:04,791 --> 00:09:06,625
[KUBOYASU]
I was once a delinquent too,

219
00:09:06,708 --> 00:09:08,208
but when I transferred schools,

220
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:10,333
I decided to give the
straight and narrow a chance.

221
00:09:10,416 --> 00:09:12,125
Bastard!

222
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:14,750
It's not always easy leaving
that old life behind, though.

223
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:17,125
Hard to hold back
when someone picks a fight,

224
00:09:17,208 --> 00:09:20,416
whether it's with me
or with one of my friends!

225
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:21,625
Aah.

226
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:23,666
Kuboyasu, you saved me.

227
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:25,208
[SAIKI] This would be
more heart-warming

228
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:27,375
if he hadn't left
a trail of bodies in his wake.

229
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:28,958
[KUBOYASU]
You knew about me.

230
00:09:29,041 --> 00:09:32,916
Of course I did. No one can hide
from my divine magic eyes.

231
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,291
I thought I blended pretty well
as a normal kid.

232
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:38,250
Even though he knew my past,
he still told me to run.

233
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,166
[KAIDOU]
I don't care about your past.

234
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:43,166
All that matters to me now
is the present and the future.

235
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,916
--Right.
--Aah!

236
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,666
[SAIKI]
He's so weak.

237
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,708
[SAIKI]
Which card has Yumehara?

238
00:09:48,791 --> 00:09:50,125
Use your x-ray vision.

239
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:54,958
♪

240
00:09:56,541 --> 00:09:59,000
[NENDOU] They're closed?
Well, that's weird.

241
00:09:59,083 --> 00:10:01,500
I can't believe you made us
walk 30 minutes for this.

242
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:03,958
Hey, don't blame the manager.
He's got hay fever.

243
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:05,833
That's serious stuff, dude.

244
00:10:05,916 --> 00:10:07,958
Can't be sneezing around
exposed noodles. Ahchoo!

245
00:10:08,041 --> 00:10:10,500
Aah. I'm mad at you for not
picking a closer ramen place.

246
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:12,083
Well, I'm going home.

247
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:14,333
Fine. Let's go find
somewhere else to hang out.

248
00:10:14,416 --> 00:10:16,541
Hey, an arcade. Let's go there.

249
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,416
How are games
a replacement for ramen?

250
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:20,875
It's not my fault
the guy has hay fever.

251
00:10:20,958 --> 00:10:23,208
Do you have any idea how
terrible that disease can get?

252
00:10:23,291 --> 00:10:26,125
My point is, we need to find
a new food place, not an arcade.

253
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:27,541
All right, then, Kaidou.

254
00:10:27,625 --> 00:10:29,708
Let's settle this beef
between us once and for all.

255
00:10:29,791 --> 00:10:31,125
Fine. I was getting bored

256
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:33,500
of having this peaceful
everyday life, anyway.

257
00:10:33,583 --> 00:10:35,041
[BOTH]
To the video arcade!

258
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:36,875
[SAIKI]
Hey, you agree on something.

259
00:10:36,958 --> 00:10:39,125
Anyway, it's been a while
since I been to an arcade.

260
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:41,791
I liked it as a kid,
so my mom always took me.

261
00:10:41,875 --> 00:10:43,500
My favorite game
was Whac-A-Mole.

262
00:10:43,583 --> 00:10:45,916
I know it's simple, but I liked
that it just let you focus on

263
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,291
doing that one thing very well,
which I did.

264
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:51,208
When I hit those moles,
they never came back up.

265
00:10:51,291 --> 00:10:53,916
All right.
I'm way ahead of the other cars.

266
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,583
Hey, how come
it's not turning right?

267
00:10:55,666 --> 00:10:56,791
[SAIKI] Put a coin in.

268
00:10:56,875 --> 00:10:58,250
I picked a broken machine again.

269
00:10:58,333 --> 00:10:59,791
[SAIKI] It's your brain
that's broken.

270
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:01,125
Is that the best
you can do, zombies?

271
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:02,958
If you couldn't handle
the pressure,

272
00:11:03,041 --> 00:11:05,083
you shouldn't have gone against
Kaido, the double bullet.

273
00:11:05,166 --> 00:11:07,708
No, I'm all out.
Let me reload. Don't eat me.

274
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:09,916
Give me a fighting chance.

275
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,916
Oh, right. Then I'm done playing
your stupid zombie game.

276
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,750
--It's totally rigged.
--Well, it is a game.

277
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,750
[laughs]
You suck at games, dude.

278
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:18,041
Fine, then let's start
this duel.

279
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:19,625
I'm ready when you are, runt.

280
00:11:19,708 --> 00:11:22,041
Just pick a game so I can start
beating the crap out of you.

281
00:11:22,125 --> 00:11:23,583
Yeah, right.
You couldn't beat me

282
00:11:23,666 --> 00:11:25,833
at a single game in this arcade,
but since it's closest,

283
00:11:25,916 --> 00:11:27,250
why don't we go with
this quiz one?

284
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:28,916
[SAIKI] Wow, you really
want to win this.

285
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,625
If you just want a game
that's close to us,

286
00:11:30,708 --> 00:11:32,250
what about the one
you're leaning on?

287
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:34,000
[SAIKI]
And you dug your own grave.

288
00:11:34,083 --> 00:11:36,125
Uh, maybe it's better
if we let Saiki choose.

289
00:11:36,208 --> 00:11:38,375
Oh, no. If you're not
gonna pick, I will.

290
00:11:38,458 --> 00:11:40,250
Just play something, seriously.

291
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:41,625
[MAN] Air hockey.

292
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:43,875
First man to nine points
is the winner.

293
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:46,416
Yeah! Air hockey is awesome!

294
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,291
[KAIDOU] I can hold my own
against most,

295
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:50,125
but Nendou's
got the strength of an ogre.

296
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:52,208
If I don't play flawlessly,
I'll get smoked.

297
00:11:52,291 --> 00:11:54,250
I need to outthink him
with strategy.

298
00:11:54,333 --> 00:11:56,125
--[MAN] Game start.
--If I hit the puck straight,

299
00:11:56,208 --> 00:11:58,416
he'll just block it
with his wild reflexes.

300
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,708
Just start.

301
00:11:59,791 --> 00:12:01,291
I'll confuse him
with a rare bank shot.

302
00:12:01,375 --> 00:12:04,583
--[SAIKI] Everyone does that.
--Tall hammer shot.

303
00:12:04,666 --> 00:12:05,958
--Bam!
--What the...? How?

304
00:12:06,041 --> 00:12:08,125
That was so fast,
I barely saw it.

305
00:12:08,208 --> 00:12:09,833
[laughs]
What's wrong, short stuff?

306
00:12:09,916 --> 00:12:12,458
Hmm. I actually did
pick this game randomly,

307
00:12:12,541 --> 00:12:15,041
but Nendou might have too much
raw strength over Kaidou.

308
00:12:15,125 --> 00:12:17,083
I can't believe
it's come to this.

309
00:12:17,166 --> 00:12:20,916
That's the same attack you tried
last time, only way slower.

310
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,833
How'd you get two
of those hitty thingies?

311
00:12:22,916 --> 00:12:24,958
Behold the impregnable wall
of double mallets.

312
00:12:25,041 --> 00:12:26,625
That's cheating,
but it doesn't matter,

313
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:28,000
because Nendou still scored.

314
00:12:28,083 --> 00:12:30,166
Ha! You haven't seen
anything yet.

315
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:31,166
Damn.

316
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:33,125
--Huh?
--What's up?

317
00:12:33,208 --> 00:12:35,416
Can't find the puck. Can you
check if it's on your side?

318
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:36,625
Uh...

319
00:12:36,708 --> 00:12:37,833
--Meteor smash!
--Aah!

320
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:39,166
[SAIKI]
That's dirty.

321
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:41,291
Looks like it was on
your side after all.

322
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:42,833
Sorry to interrupt
your victory pose,

323
00:12:42,916 --> 00:12:44,500
but you cheated again.

324
00:12:44,583 --> 00:12:46,833
I'll let it slide to keep you
from losing so badly.

325
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:48,416
[MAN]
Kaidou kept confusing Nendou

326
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,750
with more illegal,
but sneaky, plays.

327
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:53,166
--Teruhashi.
--Uh, wow.

328
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:55,625
Oh, that's weird.
You cracked the puck.

329
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:57,000
Yo, manager. We need a--

330
00:12:57,083 --> 00:13:00,333
Triple mallets.
Triple mallets featuring bag.

331
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:02,416
[MAN] Kaidou ran up his score
despite lacking skill,

332
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,916
but Nendou
was not going away quietly.

333
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,375
And so it came down
to the final point.

334
00:13:07,458 --> 00:13:09,500
The air-hockey battle
had reached its climax.

335
00:13:09,583 --> 00:13:12,375
[pants] I will say,
you played a pretty good game,

336
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:13,750
but it's over now.

337
00:13:13,833 --> 00:13:15,375
Zig-zag attack!

338
00:13:15,458 --> 00:13:17,541
It's too fast.
He'll win the game with this.

339
00:13:17,625 --> 00:13:19,375
All I can do is--
Oh, it's slowing down.

340
00:13:19,458 --> 00:13:20,583
Well, take that.

341
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:22,208
Ha-ha! Piece of cake.

342
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,916
He fell for it.
Mallet bullet attack.

343
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,166
[SAIKI]
Play dirty to the end.

344
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:27,625
[MAN]
Game, set, match.

345
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:30,000
All right, I actually won.
How do you like me now?

346
00:13:30,083 --> 00:13:32,166
And don't say I played dirty,
because no matter what,

347
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:33,583
a win is a win.

348
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:36,208
Oh, now I get it. I didn't
realize until just now

349
00:13:36,291 --> 00:13:39,083
I could use those little hitty
thingies to block the puck.

350
00:13:39,166 --> 00:13:41,000
Oh, why do I feel so guilty?

351
00:13:41,083 --> 00:13:43,208
So in a way, Nendou wins.

352
00:13:43,291 --> 00:13:45,375
Hey, I just realized
I didn't use my powers.

353
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:48,041
Oh, well. No reason to meddle in
such a hallowed sporting event.

354
00:13:48,125 --> 00:13:50,625
Hey, buddy, let's get a shot
to remember this.

355
00:13:50,708 --> 00:13:52,000
Hurry up. We're waiting.

356
00:13:52,083 --> 00:13:53,750
[SAIKI] Do I have to?

357
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:56,708
These guys are hopeless.

358
00:13:56,791 --> 00:13:59,458
♪

359
00:14:01,791 --> 00:14:03,500
Where'd that idiot go?

360
00:14:03,583 --> 00:14:05,333
I haven't seen Nendou all day.

361
00:14:05,416 --> 00:14:07,166
Wait, I forgot to buy
this week's <i>Jump.</i>

362
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:08,583
Let me pop in there quick.

363
00:14:08,666 --> 00:14:10,083
Welcome, friend.

364
00:14:10,166 --> 00:14:11,750
--Nendou?
--Oh, hey, guys.

365
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,333
Wait. You have a job?

366
00:14:13,416 --> 00:14:16,250
I didn't say anything because I
only started yesterday.

367
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:18,250
He's in the workforce.
That's bad.

368
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:19,333
[groaning]

369
00:14:19,416 --> 00:14:21,291
--Is he gonna be okay?
--Of course not.

370
00:14:21,375 --> 00:14:23,416
This is a convenience store.
It can't be that hard--

371
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,541
Hey, just because it's small
doesn't mean that it's easy.

372
00:14:25,625 --> 00:14:27,958
There's always something to be
done in a convenience store.

373
00:14:28,041 --> 00:14:30,125
Selling lottery tickets,
running copies,

374
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:32,250
stocking shelves,
topping off the deep fryer.

375
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:33,833
--It's overwhelming.
-Oh, you're smart.

376
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,125
Have you worked in one before?

377
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:37,041
Yeah, after I wrecked
my motorcycle.

378
00:14:37,125 --> 00:14:38,750
Hey, he got a customer.

379
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:40,583
Looks like 500 yen
worth of stuff.

380
00:14:40,666 --> 00:14:41,916
What? You're guessing at it?

381
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,375
Use the register!
Use the register.

382
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:46,125
I'd like to,
but I couldn't open the drawer,

383
00:14:46,208 --> 00:14:48,125
so I tried some stuff,
and now it's broke.

384
00:14:48,208 --> 00:14:50,875
[KUBOYASU] Use the other one.
Here, watch and learn.

385
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:52,791
Sir, I'll ring you up over here.

386
00:14:52,875 --> 00:14:55,166
That comes to 777 yen, please.

387
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:57,583
Oh, three sevens.
That's lucky, sir or ma'am.

388
00:14:57,666 --> 00:15:00,416
For a prize, please enjoy
this free box of fried chicken.

389
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:01,958
[KUBOYASU]
Don't give away product.

390
00:15:02,041 --> 00:15:05,250
Your change is 333 yen.
Thank you. Come again.

391
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,833
[SAIKI] But that wasn't
the correct change at all.

392
00:15:07,916 --> 00:15:09,833
--an I get this issue of <i>Jump?</i>
--Beep.

393
00:15:09,916 --> 00:15:12,666
Why do you need to check my age?
It's just a copy of <i>Shonen Jump.</i>

394
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:14,541
Hey, Nendou, are all these boys
friends of yours?

395
00:15:14,625 --> 00:15:16,750
--Yes, Mr. Manager.
--Sorry for using the register.

396
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:19,416
It's fine. A long as you're
Nendou's friends, I trust you.

397
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:22,125
This might sound crazy,
but I owe my life to Nendou.

398
00:15:22,208 --> 00:15:23,708
He helped me a few weeks back

399
00:15:23,791 --> 00:15:26,166
when I collapsed on the street
with severe heart palpitations.

400
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:27,583
I offered to repay him
however I could,

401
00:15:27,666 --> 00:15:29,125
and he said
he was looking for a job.

402
00:15:29,208 --> 00:15:30,333
That's how we got
where we are.

403
00:15:30,416 --> 00:15:31,791
[SAIKI]
Yeah, that makes sense.

404
00:15:31,875 --> 00:15:33,166
Nendou, I am so grateful

405
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:34,875
for everything you've done.
Thank you.

406
00:15:34,958 --> 00:15:36,375
--Aw...
--And you're fired.

407
00:15:36,458 --> 00:15:37,875
What?

408
00:15:37,958 --> 00:15:40,083
You broke the register three
times and the copier twice.

409
00:15:40,166 --> 00:15:41,541
Your tills are short 33,000 yen,

410
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:43,791
and we've gotten
27 complaints from customers.

411
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:46,458
Sorry, Nendou, but I'd rather be
indebted to you forever

412
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:48,375
than have to employ you
in my store.

413
00:15:48,458 --> 00:15:51,000
[SAIKI] That was
the kind of a sped-up plot

414
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:52,708
that only happens in fiction.

415
00:15:52,791 --> 00:15:56,041
Don't go crying for me, guys.
At least I have my other job.

416
00:15:56,125 --> 00:15:57,333
--What?
--Other job?

417
00:15:57,416 --> 00:16:00,083
Oh, hey there, Riki.
You're early.

418
00:16:00,166 --> 00:16:01,958
--A ramen shop?
--It's his favorite food.

419
00:16:02,041 --> 00:16:04,791
I got fired from my other job,
so I figured I'd come in early.

420
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:07,500
It was a convenience store,
and I made a lot of mistakes,

421
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:08,666
and I scared shoppers.

422
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:11,000
I want you to put
all that crap behind you

423
00:16:11,083 --> 00:16:12,541
and get ready
so you can work for me.

424
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:14,916
Listen good, kid.
Everyone makes mistakes.

425
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,291
And looks don't matter.

426
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:17,750
What's important
is you're enthusiastic.

427
00:16:17,833 --> 00:16:20,041
Be like that,
you'll always have a job here.

428
00:16:20,125 --> 00:16:22,416
Or not, yeah.

429
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:23,625
You're fired.

430
00:16:23,708 --> 00:16:24,958
[wind howls]

431
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:26,458
Here. You were holding two jobs

432
00:16:26,541 --> 00:16:28,416
so you could earn enough
to buy these for yourself.

433
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,458
--You like them, don't you?
--That's not what I wanted!

434
00:16:30,541 --> 00:16:32,250
My mom's birthday is next week.

435
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:34,083
That's why I was trying to
save up some money.

436
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:35,416
[KAIDOU] Oh, I didn't know.

437
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,041
See, since I don't have a dad
no more,

438
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:39,083
my mom has to work all the time
to support me.

439
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:41,000
She holds down
three different jobs

440
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:43,583
and still finds time to cook
for me and clean all my clothes.

441
00:16:43,666 --> 00:16:46,250
That's not an easy life,
so I wanted to show my love

442
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:48,125
by buying her a present
with my own money.

443
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:49,958
Hey, what are you guys
crying about over there?

444
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:51,458
[SAIKI] Ignore those idiots.

445
00:16:51,541 --> 00:16:53,250
--I'm not crying.
--If you want another job...

446
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:55,250
the diner by the train station
is hiring.

447
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,666
We could all go apply together.

448
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:59,250
--[NENDOU] Yeah, cool.
--I'm going home.

449
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:02,083
[MANAGER] I'd like you meet
our new waiters--

450
00:17:02,166 --> 00:17:03,583
Kaidou, Kuboyasu,

451
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:05,041
and Rikii.

452
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:06,833
[BOTH]
Nendou didn't get the job?

453
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:09,416
What's the point of working here
if Nendou's not gonna be here?

454
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,125
We forgot that no restaurant
would ever hire

455
00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:13,083
someone as ugly as he is
to be a waiter.

456
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:14,541
All right, guys,
let's make some money.

457
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:16,166
Wait. Who the hell
do you think you are?

458
00:17:16,250 --> 00:17:17,791
Let me explain.

459
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:20,083
I knew Nendou's looks guaranteed
he wouldn't get hired,

460
00:17:20,166 --> 00:17:21,333
so I took action.

461
00:17:21,416 --> 00:17:23,375
Hey, I didn't see you there.

462
00:17:23,458 --> 00:17:26,208
[SAIKI] I made it so he appears
handsomer than he really is.

463
00:17:26,291 --> 00:17:28,708
Riki Nendou is now
just Rikii with two "i"s.

464
00:17:28,791 --> 00:17:31,291
--Of course Nendou has no clue.
--Hey, Rikii.

465
00:17:31,375 --> 00:17:33,166
Don't call me by my first name.
It's weird.

466
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:35,458
[SAIKI] I even changed
the spelling on his application.

467
00:17:35,541 --> 00:17:36,625
Rikki!

468
00:17:36,708 --> 00:17:38,250
You're pouring water
on that customer.

469
00:17:38,333 --> 00:17:40,333
I'll let you guys
clean this up.

470
00:17:40,416 --> 00:17:42,333
[BOTH] I'm sorry.
Please forgive us, sir.

471
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:44,625
How'd we get stuck cleaning some
random employee's mess?

472
00:17:44,708 --> 00:17:45,708
Aah! I'm sorry!

473
00:17:45,791 --> 00:17:47,458
Kaidou,
you're screwing up now too?

474
00:17:47,541 --> 00:17:50,500
Part-timer, get us some ketchup
for these french fries.

475
00:17:50,583 --> 00:17:52,000
[CUSTOMER]
Lickety-split, dumbbell.

476
00:17:52,083 --> 00:17:53,833
[FRENCH FRY CUSTOMER]
You ain't getting no tip.

477
00:17:53,916 --> 00:17:56,625
Oh, I'll get you some ketchup...
out of your nose.

478
00:17:56,708 --> 00:17:58,833
Here's a tip.
Don't mess with me!

479
00:17:58,916 --> 00:18:01,791
How are they so hopeless?

480
00:18:01,875 --> 00:18:03,166
[BOY] Come on.

481
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:05,000
[YUMEHARA] You mean Saiki
does like me?

482
00:18:05,083 --> 00:18:06,791
Nope, not a chance.

483
00:18:06,875 --> 00:18:09,041
♪

484
00:18:11,666 --> 00:18:14,041
[SAIKI] At least once a winter,
it happens:

485
00:18:14,125 --> 00:18:15,583
a gym class so cold,

486
00:18:15,666 --> 00:18:17,625
it makes you want to strangle
any teacher in a jacket.

487
00:18:17,708 --> 00:18:20,250
All right, get it together.
Time for the winter marathon.

488
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:21,791
[SAIKI]
That's right, marathon.

489
00:18:21,875 --> 00:18:24,833
But, actually, this is easiest
of impossible for me.

490
00:18:24,916 --> 00:18:26,291
All I have to do is run,

491
00:18:26,375 --> 00:18:28,500
and I can even use
my pyrokinesis to stay warm.

492
00:18:28,583 --> 00:18:30,791
--You'll warm up once we start.
--Where's your jacket?

493
00:18:30,875 --> 00:18:32,833
--Hairo, aren't you freezing?
--Ha! Not at all.

494
00:18:32,916 --> 00:18:35,375
--See, look. I've got sleeves.
--[SAIKI] Does that help?

495
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:38,000
It drops a few degrees,
and you wimps all start whining?

496
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:39,500
Hairo, is that all
you're wearing?

497
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:41,708
He's cheating
with fleece bandages.

498
00:18:41,791 --> 00:18:43,041
Man, I'm tired...

499
00:18:43,125 --> 00:18:44,708
Let's ignore Nendou
in this video.

500
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:47,000
Hey, Nendou. Would you like
to be running buddies today?

501
00:18:47,083 --> 00:18:48,625
Yeah, that sounds fun.

502
00:18:48,708 --> 00:18:50,666
Time we settle this and see
who's the better athlete.

503
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:52,875
I will have revenge
for the physical fitness test.

504
00:18:52,958 --> 00:18:55,000
--It's getting warm here.
--Like a furnace.

505
00:18:55,083 --> 00:18:57,833
This is a 10K race. Every 2K,
you'll cross a checkpoint

506
00:18:57,916 --> 00:19:00,541
with a teacher at it making sure
there's no funny business.

507
00:19:00,625 --> 00:19:04,416
Well, sorry about this, but
I'm gonna let out my true power.

508
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:05,833
See you at the finish line.

509
00:19:05,916 --> 00:19:07,375
Ready? Start.

510
00:19:07,458 --> 00:19:11,250
Ha-ha! So long, mortals.
Hey, wait, Slow down.

511
00:19:11,333 --> 00:19:14,291
You fools. Running fast
from the start will...

512
00:19:14,375 --> 00:19:15,750
tire you out.

513
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,458
I'll be waiting for you
at the finish line,

514
00:19:17,541 --> 00:19:19,041
even after throwing the race.

515
00:19:19,125 --> 00:19:21,958
Right now, I'm in 45th place
out of 90 students.

516
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:23,333
At this pace, I'll finish

517
00:19:23,416 --> 00:19:25,166
without drawing any attention
to myself.

518
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:26,541
[huff and puffs]

519
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:28,208
He's nowhere in sight.

520
00:19:28,291 --> 00:19:30,458
All I got to do is stay at
this pace, and I'll finish--

521
00:19:30,541 --> 00:19:33,458
Hey, you're fast. I went to buy
a drink, and you were gone.

522
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:35,083
Wait. You stopped at
a convenience store,

523
00:19:35,166 --> 00:19:36,833
and you still caught up with me?

524
00:19:36,916 --> 00:19:39,666
It's important to stay hydrated
when you're running a marathon.

525
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:40,708
Corn potage?

526
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:42,333
Oh, yeah.
This warms me right up.

527
00:19:42,416 --> 00:19:45,250
Damn it! Sweet.
Eight kilometers left.

528
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:47,333
Huh? Guess I should
get a sweat going

529
00:19:47,416 --> 00:19:50,250
so they don't become suspicious.

530
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:52,750
[pants]
Saiki, you're going too fast.

531
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:54,208
I'm impressed
he made it this far

532
00:19:54,291 --> 00:19:55,791
considering how weak he is.

533
00:19:55,875 --> 00:19:57,708
--Get in.
--But what if we get caught?

534
00:19:57,791 --> 00:20:00,125
Don't worry. We'll get out
before the checkpoint. Hurry up.

535
00:20:00,208 --> 00:20:01,541
[SAIKI] Three idiots.

536
00:20:01,625 --> 00:20:03,333
--Where to?
--Eight kilometers towards the--

537
00:20:03,416 --> 00:20:05,625
School. Start the race
from the beginning.

538
00:20:05,708 --> 00:20:07,208
[all gasp]

539
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:09,583
[SAIKI] So there's a go-back-
to-start square in real life.

540
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:12,500
[MAN] So Saiki passed the second
checkpoint without incident.

541
00:20:12,583 --> 00:20:14,333
He's now closing in on
the 6K mark,

542
00:20:14,416 --> 00:20:15,750
still in the middle of the pack.

543
00:20:15,833 --> 00:20:16,916
Four more to go, kiddos.

544
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,583
How is he at
every checkpoint like that?

545
00:20:19,666 --> 00:20:22,750
Hmm? A lot of guys
are dropping out now.

546
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:24,208
What's going on?

547
00:20:24,291 --> 00:20:25,791
See, Saiki? I warned them

548
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:27,875
if they went too fast
at the start, they'd just--

549
00:20:27,958 --> 00:20:29,125
[throws up]

550
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:30,541
[SAIKI]
At least they're not puking.

551
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:33,416
I can't do this.
I got nothing left in the tank.

552
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:36,416
Now I have to try to keep pace
with Hairo and Nendou.

553
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,125
Oh, I see. Were all these guys

554
00:20:38,208 --> 00:20:40,833
try to keep up with those two
idiots? That's pretty reckless.

555
00:20:40,916 --> 00:20:43,291
[winded] Saiki,
if everyone's taking a break,

556
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:44,958
there's no shame
in us resting too.

557
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:47,208
As it stands,
I'll finish with a high rank.

558
00:20:47,291 --> 00:20:48,833
Well, desperate times.

559
00:20:48,916 --> 00:20:52,541
What's happening?
I don't even feel tired anymore.

560
00:20:52,625 --> 00:20:54,333
Saiki, I've been reborn.

561
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:56,625
I'm back in the hunt.
First place is--

562
00:20:56,708 --> 00:20:58,500
I turned back time on your body.

563
00:20:58,583 --> 00:21:01,458
Oh. Well, I could run
another 10K.

564
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:03,625
All their energy
is coming back in a rush

565
00:21:03,708 --> 00:21:06,291
because I'm basically resetting
their exhaustion levels to zero.

566
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:08,666
Come back to life, zombies.

567
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:11,333
Look, our first finisher's
coming in. It's Hairo.

568
00:21:11,416 --> 00:21:12,625
No, wait. Who's that?

569
00:21:12,708 --> 00:21:15,041
No! What the heck
is fueling this guy?

570
00:21:15,125 --> 00:21:17,500
He's running backward,
and I still can't pass him.

571
00:21:17,583 --> 00:21:20,458
It's like he's not even human.
I can't keep up.

572
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:23,208
I'm barely moving my legs.
I'm gonna lose.

573
00:21:23,291 --> 00:21:24,875
I'm gonna... win!

574
00:21:24,958 --> 00:21:27,541
Hey, look. It's manga author--
Shuichi Aso!

575
00:21:27,625 --> 00:21:30,416
What? Where? Wait. Hairo.

576
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:32,375
Hey, where's that Aso guy
and who is he?

577
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:33,625
Second place: Nendou.

578
00:21:33,708 --> 00:21:36,166
--I won.
--[SAIKI] But did you really?

579
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:37,875
[indistinct chatter]

580
00:21:37,958 --> 00:21:39,458
Huh? Saiki?

581
00:21:39,541 --> 00:21:41,750
I thought there was a bigger gap
between me and everyone else.

582
00:21:41,833 --> 00:21:43,208
The gap would've been
much larger

583
00:21:43,291 --> 00:21:44,416
if I hadn't restored them all,

584
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:45,708
but the real winner
is Matsuzaki.

585
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:47,458
--He was everywhere.
--Yeah!

586
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:49,708
--That's some good running.
--[SAIKI] That's impressive.

587
00:21:49,791 --> 00:21:53,750
At least I got my boring
45th-place finish like I wanted.

588
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:55,041
Forty-four.

589
00:21:55,125 --> 00:21:58,416
Weird. I could swear
there were 44 ahead of me.

590
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:00,083
Did I pass someone and forget?

591
00:22:00,166 --> 00:22:01,291
I'm tired again.

592
00:22:01,375 --> 00:22:02,833
[MAN] In case you're curious,

593
00:22:02,916 --> 00:22:04,666
the girls' marathon
was held later in the week.

594
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:06,458
The checkpoints
will have snacks and stuff.

595
00:22:06,541 --> 00:22:08,291
[GIRL] Never too early
to start work on my beach body.

596
00:22:08,375 --> 00:22:11,708
When you're a perfect pretty
girl, marathons also come easy.

597
00:22:11,791 --> 00:22:14,666
♪

598
00:23:41,666 --> 00:23:44,083
Hi. I'm Kokomi Teruhashi.

599
00:23:44,166 --> 00:23:46,500
Thank you so much for watching
the hilarious anime

600
00:23:46,583 --> 00:23:48,208
<i>The Disastrous Life</i>
<i>of Saiki K.,</i>

601
00:23:48,291 --> 00:23:49,833
short for Kunio.

602
00:23:49,916 --> 00:23:52,250
Wait. It's Kusuo, and you're
saying I visit his house

603
00:23:52,333 --> 00:23:53,958
and do karaoke next episode?

604
00:23:54,041 --> 00:23:56,708
Everyone'll say, "Oh, wow,"
when they hear me sing.

